orks of Darwin and Wallace, this work appears here for the first time in a complete English-language translation. Covering far more than its title implies, it represents the first articulation of an integrative “science of the earth, ” encompassing most of today’s environmental sciences. Ecologist Stephen T. Jackson introduces the treatise and explains its enduring significance two centuries after its publication.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aPhysical geography. 0aPhytogeography. 0aPlant ecology. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  achurch, poe, thoreau, goethe, emerson, science, exploration, expedition, travelogue, nonfiction, history, botany, biology, aime bonpland, south america, natural sciences, environmentalism, nature, environment, physical geography, ecology, plants, phytogeography, alexander von humboldt, research, biodiversity, species, conservation.1 aBonpland, Aimé, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBonpland, Aimé, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHumboldt, Alexander von, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJackson, Stephen T.1 aJackson, Stephen T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJackson, Stephen T., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRomanowski, Sylvie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRomanowski, Sylvie.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226360683423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226360683/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles